  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large dolsot stone bowl over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and grated ginger, cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the lamb shoulder and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the cumin, coriander, cinnamon, salt, and black pepper. Stir to combine.",
    "Add 2 cups of water to the bowl and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 1.5 hours, or until the lamb is tender.",
    "Stir in the rose water and continue to simmer for 10 minutes.",
    "Serve the lamb and sauce hot, garnished with chopped fresh parsley and a dollop of yogurt.",
    "Serve with crusty bread or over couscous, if desired."
  ],
